	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1" facs="EHRI-ET-JMP003_01.jpg"/>
			<p>My Dears,</p>

			<p>We are overjoyed that we are finally in <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-716"
					type="subject">written touch</term> with you and that we can write to you in our mother tongue. We have so much to tell you that
				there isn’t enough paper in the world that could contain it all. Unfortunately, it’s mostly all bad news. So little of it is good. As
				you have perhaps already learned from Maruška, out of our whole family only <persName ref="#ehri_et_hellerova_jana">Hanka</persName>
				and I returned, but we are happy that at least the two of us were reunited. I must tell you all about our departure from <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/3067696/prague.html">Prague</placeName>. As you know, <persName
					ref="http://www.holocaust.cz/databaze-obeti/obet/119939-egon-sachs/" type="victim">Kurt</persName> and I were transported to
					<placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_ghettos-449" type="ghetto">Theresienstadt</placeName> in <date
					when="1943-07">July 1943</date> to be with our <pb n="2" facs="EHRI-ET-JMP003_02.jpg"/> parents and <persName
					ref="#ehri_et_hellerova_jana">Hanka</persName>. We were together there for 1 ¼ years. We were doing rather well, all told.
					<persName ref="http://www.holocaust.cz/databaze-obeti/obet/119939-egon-sachs/" type="victim">Kurt</persName> and my parents worked
				in the office, <persName ref="#ehri_et_hellerova_jana">Hanka</persName> in the bakery, and I mostly did nothing because I was <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-292" type="subject">sick</term>. Then, in the fall of <date when="1944"
					>1944</date>, we were gradually <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-267" type="subject"
					>transported</term> — <persName ref="http://www.holocaust.cz/databaze-obeti/obet/92804-artur-heller/" type="victim"
					>father</persName> left separately, <persName ref="http://www.holocaust.cz/databaze-obeti/obet/92826-edita-hellerova/"
					type="victim">mother</persName> with <persName ref="#ehri_et_hellerova_jana">Hanka</persName>, and I with <persName
					ref="http://www.holocaust.cz/databaze-obeti/obet/119939-egon-sachs/" type="victim">Kurt</persName>. All of the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-267" type="subject">transports</term> went to <placeName
					type="camp" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-2">Auschwitz</placeName>. You cannot imagine what we suffered
				through. I don’t want to describe our experiences and so it’s perhaps a little cruel of me to write and tell you so directly that our
				dear <persName ref="http://www.holocaust.cz/databaze-obeti/obet/92826-edita-hellerova/" type="victim">mother</persName>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">died</term> there. <persName
					ref="http://www.holocaust.cz/databaze-obeti/obet/92804-artur-heller/" type="victim">Father</persName>, who successfully made it
				past the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-411" type="subject">selection</term> process, was <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">shot</term> on the <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/8505031/czechoslovakia.html">Czech</placeName> border on <date when="1945-05-03">May 3rd,
				1945</date>, just 5 days before the end of the <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1080"
					>war</term>, during the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-623" type="subject">evacuation</term> of the
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-508" type="subject">labor camp</term> where he was sent. <persName
					ref="http://www.holocaust.cz/databaze-obeti/obet/119939-egon-sachs/" type="victim">Kurt</persName> was separated from me in
					<placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_ghettos-449" type="ghetto">Theresienstadt</placeName> near the train
				and it was only when I returned to <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3067696/prague.html">Prague</placeName> that I learned that
				he was held for about 3 weeks in the <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-places-place-jmp-49">Small
					Fortress</placeName> and was supposedly <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject"
					>shot</term> there. We are positive regarding <persName ref="http://www.holocaust.cz/databaze-obeti/obet/92804-artur-heller/"
					>father</persName> since he was with <persName ref="#ehri_et_hellerova_jana">Hanka</persName>’s young <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826">man</term>, who returned. Jirka also returned and we’re <term
					type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837">living</term> together with him now. I ran into
					<persName ref="#ehri_et_hellerova_jana">Hanka</persName> by happy chance in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/3067696/prague.html">Prague</placeName>. She had come back one month earlier than I and she no longer
				believed that I would return. I’m sure you can imagine what our <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-831">life</term> is like now. Our financial situation is miserable; we
				don’t have enough <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-836">clothes</term> to wear. <pb n="3"
					facs="EHRI-ET-JMP003_03.jpg"/> I’ll likely find an office job. <persName ref="#ehri_et_hellerova_jana">Hanka</persName> is
				graduating in <date when="1945-09">September</date> and then she’ll probably make her living as an illustrator. In short, this is all
				that we wanted to tell you about what we went through. We don’t know what the future holds. We are in touch with Maruška. Her little
				Jana is so adorable. We have visited them several times. Please write us soon and let us know if you are coming. We would love to see
				you, we have so much to tell. You can’t imagine how we are faring. But at least we are happy that you will come and see us.</p>
		</body>
	</text>
